==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[wicca#Old English|wiċċa]] {{m}}, [[wicce|wiċċe]] {{f}}.
===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: wĭch
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /wɪʧ/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /wItS/

====Homophones====
*[[which]] (''depends on accent'')

===Noun===
'''witch''' (plural: '''witches''')

#A (usually female) person who uses [[magic]].
#(''derogatory'') An ugly or unpleasant woman.
#:''I hate that old witch.''

